<h2>Why Choose a Tourmaline Engagement Ring?</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Uniqueness:</strong> No two tourmaline stones are the same — each is a natural original.</li>
  <li><strong>Emotional Symbolism:</strong> Green tourmaline is said to symbolize healing and life energy, while pink tourmaline embodies love and compassion.</li>
  <li><strong>Affordability:</strong> Tourmaline offers a high-end look at a fraction of the price of diamonds.</li>
  <li><strong>Ethical Sourcing:</strong> Tourmalines are easier to trace to responsible mines than many diamonds.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Tourmaline Colors and Their Meanings</h2>
<p>
Each color of tourmaline offers a different vibe. Here's how couples are choosing based on color energy:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Green Tourmaline:</strong> Nature-inspired, calming, and perfect for grounded personalities.</li>
  <li><strong>Pink Tourmaline:</strong> Feminine, romantic, and playful.</li>
  <li><strong>Watermelon Tourmaline:</strong> A combination of pink & green — symbolizing emotional balance and harmony.</li>
  <li><strong>Paraiba Tourmaline:</strong> Rare and electric blue-green — for those who love something bold.</li>
</ul>

