<h2>🧠 FAQ: What Do People Ask About Tourmaline Rings?</h2>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> Is tourmaline a good stone for an engagement ring?<br />
<strong>A:</strong> Yes! While not as hard as diamond, it’s durable enough for regular wear — especially in protective settings. Plus, its uniqueness makes it ideal for couples who want something special.</p>

<p><strong>Q:</strong> What’s the most popular tourmaline color?<br />
<strong>A:</strong> Pink and green are both favorites, but watermelon tourmaline is gaining popularity for its layered symbolism.</p>

<p><strong>Q:</strong> Can I wear it daily?<br />
<strong>A:</strong> Absolutely, but like all softer gemstones, remove during heavy work and avoid knocks.</p>

